    int[] arr = {2, 4, 5};
    output :7

🔹 Core Idea (Very Important)
      We maintain a basis array:
      basis[i] → number having highest set bit at position i
      👉 Think:
        One number per bit position
        Each represents an independent XOR contributor
🔹 Algorithm Steps
    Step 1: Initialize
        int[] basis = new int[32]; // for 32 bits
    Step 2: Insert each number into basis
        For each number x:
        Try to reduce it using existing basis
        Logic:
          For bit from high → low:
            If that bit is set in x:
                If basis[bit] is empty → store x there ✅
                Else → reduce: x = x ^ basis[bit]
            
Why this complexity?
    Each number has at most log₂(max value) bits (≈ 31 for int)
    For each number, we try to reduce it using existing basis elements
    
    👉 So:Time = O(n × number of bits) = O(n × log(max))

